# Customer Segmentation using K-Means Clustering

## Project Overview

This project performs **customer segmentation using K-Means clustering** on the Online Retail dataset. The goal is to identify distinct customer groups based on purchasing behavior in order to support better marketing strategies, customer retention, and revenue growth.

By analyzing transaction data, we engineer customer-level features and apply unsupervised machine learning to group customers into meaningful segments.

---

## Business Objective

Businesses often struggle to treat all customers the same way. Customer segmentation helps answer key questions such as:

- Who are the **most valuable customers**?
- Which customers are **likely to churn**?
- Which customers buy **frequently but spend less**?
- Which groups should receive **targeted promotions**?

This project clusters customers based on purchasing patterns and provides actionable insights.

---

## Dataset

**Online Retail Dataset**

The dataset contains transactions from a UK-based online retail store between 2010 and 2011.

### Key Columns

| Column | Description |
|------|-------------|
| InvoiceNo | Transaction ID |
| StockCode | Product ID |
| Description | Product name |
| Quantity | Number of items purchased |
| InvoiceDate | Date of transaction |
| UnitPrice | Price per unit |
| CustomerID | Unique customer identifier |
| Country | Customer location |

Each row represents **a product purchased within a transaction**.

